args: It doesn't seem like the crowd has any\nintention of dispersing.
I hate to say it, but I think our only\nrecourse is to pack it up and head home.
If I stick around here, I'm going to end up\nmaking trouble for all our friends.
Do me a favor, Elisanne. Try to have at\nleast SOME fun, even if you have to do\nit alone.
Let me go. I'm nothing but a burden here.
No, you're not. I've come up with a plan.
Yes. But it'll be tough to pull off alone.\nAt the very least, I'll need three people.
Nina? Amane? I hate to ask,\nbut could you help us?
Gladly. Alex helped me\nmake a killing, after all.
I'm in, too! How could I call myself a\nbarker if I ignored two folks right here\nin desperate need of a vacation?
Much obliged. With that settled, here's\nwhat I need the two of you to do...
Okay, but who am I looking at?\nIs that Alex in disguise?
At least one of them has to be the\nreal Alex, right?
Hey, waaait! Alex! We want to thank you\nfor saving the beach!
Elisanne's late. I hope she's okay.
There you are! What a relief. You managed\nto give the fans the slip, I take it?
I did. The three of us used our disguises\nto lure the crowd and split them apart.
It took longer than I expected, but\nI'd call the plan a rousing success.
Thank you. You put yourselves at risk for\nmy sake. It means a lot.
What are you talking about? You're the\none who took risks for ME to begin with.
You took a job outside of your wheelhouse\nat the cafe, you tried to beat all the fiends\nat the beach by yourself...
That reminds me. Do you remember how\nI told you that you were trying to do too\nmuch by yourself?
Yeah. Now that you mention it, with\neverything that happened, I forgot to\nask what you were getting at.
What I wanted to say was that there's\nno need for you and you ALONE to do\nso much. I'm here too, you know.
The desire to enjoy a relaxing vacation\ntogether runs both ways. And I was ready\nto work for it.
That's why I'm delighted that I could be\nhelpful to you too with what we just did.
Elisanne...! I had no idea.\nThank you so much, truly.
You can thank me by putting some\nsunscreen on and enjoying the rest\nof this day. Do we have a deal?
This is everything I could've hoped for.\nHere's to making new summer memories!
Take that! And that!\nWell? Ready to cry uncle?
Eeek, cold! But two can play that game.\nHere's your PAYBACK!
I could say the same of you, Alex!
A little more to the left!\n...Agh, too far!
I had no idea watermelon splitting was\nthis hard. Your days are numbered, you\ngreen-and-pink menace. Let's go again!
Phew. I'm a little tired out.
We've been playing around for quite a\nwhile! Let's take a break.
The sound of the waves is so nice.\nThere's something calming about the sea.
It hasn't been easy for any of us lately.\nYou deserve to soak it all in, Alex.
Vacations aren't just about high-energy\nanticsâ€”they're also about taking time to\nrecuperate, both in body and mind.
It sounds like I'm hitting all the marks,\nthen.
I'm...so happy. Hanging out with you until\nwe're both spent, then sitting together in\npeaceful repose...
I'm never going to forget this summer...\nNot so long as I...live...
She fell asleep. And no wonder.\nIt's about time she let herself breathe.
Even her sleeping face looks happy.\nHee hee.
It does my heart good to see you making\nsummer memories at long last, Alex.\nYou deserve this. This and so much more.
